EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] *REUSE* [Player] Construction - Produce inventory + END_IllithidOptions_Assimilation Tadpole Handover
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player retrieves the supreme tadpole from their inventory. The tadpole levitates in their palm.

Text.Value: I'm dying. My heart feels like a live grenade - gonna blow any minute. You still have a life to live. I don't.
Now is the moment - make the sacrifice. Become ghaik, and wield the stones!
Gith'ka tavkim krash'ht. Your sacrifice will not be forgotten.
I know you. I know you know your own mind. If this is what you want, then all I can say is give 'em Hell, soldier.
What are you doing? The time is now!
Is'tark. You are putting us at risk!

--- thrall -
- pestilence --
-- EXTINGUISH --

--- thrall -
- pestilence --
-- EXTINGUISH --
No - neither of us is turning into a mind flayer. Not now.
Well would you look at that. If I had a bit more time, I think I could get used to this.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Player look around their body in their mind flayer form
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Karlach admires their new mind flayer form.
Player transforms into a mind flayer

Text.Value: Evolve.
*Your pulse quickens through veins, nerves, thoughts, rising to a fever pitch.*
Wait. There's another way. You know what's waiting for me - nothing but oblivion. This could be my last good deed.
Why you?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Companion hands the player the tadpole the supreme tadpole from their inventory. This can be off-screen. it's an edge case.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This is if a companion is the one who used the tadpole.

Text.Value: If this is the end for me, let me be the motherfucker who saved the world.
*Your mind and body swell as one. You are who you always were, but infinitely better.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Player look around their body in their mind flayer form
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player admires their new mind flayer form.

Text.Value: Do it. Do it now. Evolve.
You'll still go drinking with me when I've got a face full of tentacles, right?
Put the tadpole away.
You always were sensible. This heart inside me is about to blow. Doesn't matter which body it obliterates, right?
But it isn't a sacrifice. Not to me. I... I'm dying. This thing in my chest is burning me through.
Karlach, if you really want to do this, all I can say is 'thank you.'
This might be your last opportunity to evolve - do it. Now.
Let me do this for you. For me. Please, darling. I want to.
Put the tadpole away.
This is my sacrifice to make. Not yours.
Do the honourable thing - make the sacrifice. Now.
No, Karlach. This is for me to do. I'll embrace the parasite - I'll evolve.
*A gentle thing, full of promise, full of potential. It wants to evolve you.*
Remember - you have to be illithid to wield the Netherstones. Now is the time. Absorb the parasite's potential. Evolve.
Embrace the parasite - evolve.
All right. If this is what you really want, all I can say is thank you.
This is a mistake!
You are taking a HUGE risk!
What are you doing?!
*A fierce thing, burning with potential - it feels your burden, your strife. It wants to evolve you.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Karlach closes their eyes, a mindmeld effect takes over. Karlach transforms into a mind flayer. See: END_IllithidOptions_Assimilation for animation of the same moment.

Text.Value: What are you waiting for? You cannot wield the Netherstones unless you become a mind flayer.
Wait. You don't have to do this. There's another option - me.
You'll still love me when I've got a face full of tentacles, right?
Go on - open your mind to it. Complete your evolution. Become illithid.
Any time, soldier.
Better you than me.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player closes their eyes, a mindmeld effect takes over. Player transforms into a mind flayer. See: END_IllithidOptions_Assimilation for animation of the same moment.
Karlach closes their eyes, a mindmeld effect takes over. Karlach transforms into a mind flayer.

Text.Value: What are you doing? You cannot wield the Netherstones if you are not a mind flayer.
*A fierce thing, burning with potential, primed for absorption - it feels the pull of the Netherbrain, but its attention rests on you.*

Synopsis:
The player made the choice to become a Mind Flayer, but held off on transforming right away, so the Emperor gave them a supreme tadpole to use when they decided to make the switch.

Using the supreme tadpole item will trigger this dialog, which can happen in and out of combat.
